						<summary>

						<p>On a slab lying in Survey No. 91.</p>						

						<p>Circa 16th century.</p>						

						<p>It states that Salabhatakhān Sāheb conferred upon Dēvaṇagauḍa of Ālūru the honour of riding a horse with a parasol and a gift of garden free of tax.</p>						

